referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Westby","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Selmer, Alf, Erik, Eyvind, Knut, Mauritz, Orvald, Thor.","English: habitational name from any of various places called Westby, for example in Lancashire, Lincolnshire, and Yorkshire, all named with Old Norse <i>vestr</i> ‘west, western’ + <i>bý</i> ‘farmstead, village’.","Norwegian: habitational name from any of twenty or more farmsteads, mainly in southeastern Norway, named in Old Norse as <i>Vestbýr</i>, a compound Old Norse <i>vestr</i> ‘west’ + <i>býr</i> ‘settlement’. Compare 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Wesby","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Westby  ."]},{"name":"Westbay","meanings":["Americanized form of Norwegian or Swedish   Westby  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":34,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"John De Westby was born in 1421, in London, England as the son of John Westbury and Alice CARENT. He married Katherine Burleigh in 1463, in Gisburn, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1479, in Gisburn, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1421–14